name: weakly dependent matrices

name: weakly dependent m.d.s.
definition: A weakly dependent martingale difference sequence of d-vectors

name: Weakly-Dependent Panel Data
definition: Panel data where observations have limited dependence across time or units

name: weakly dependent time series
definition: A type of data structure that neighbor-excluding cross-fitting is applicable to

name: weakly sparse
definition: A sparsity condition requiring that residual effects ξi have limited non-zero components

name: weakly sparse deviation
definition: A deviation ξ_i from the dense part that is weakly sparse in nature

name: weakly sparse individual effects
definition: Assumption that individual effects in panel data are weakly sparse

name: weakly sparse vectors
definition: Vectors ξE and (δE0, β0) that satisfy sparsity conditions with parameters (νE, SE) and (νE, N−νE/2SE) respectively

name: Weakly targeted design
definition: A synthetic control design variant that is weakly targeted

name: Weakly-targeted design
definition: A design approach with best performance at intermediate values of β and ξ

name: Weak mixing
definition: Condition on dependence structure of stochastic processes

name: Weak sparsity
definition: Vectors δP₀ and ξ are (ν,S)-weakly sparse with specified sparsity parameters S

name: weak sparsity assumption
definition: Assumption that the vector of unobserved unit effects is well approximated by a sparse vector with small number of non-zero components

name: Weak sparsity parameters
definition: Parameters (ν, SP) that characterize the sparsity of decompositions and determine convergence rates

name: weak unconfoundedness
definition: Requires that the indicator for receiving a particular treatment level and the potential outcome for that treatment level are conditionally independent given covariates

name: weekly averages
definition: aggregation of price and quantity sold data at weekly frequency

name: weekly sales
definition: Sales data aggregated on a weekly basis

name: weight
definition: A value assigned to edges in a network that may correspond to distances, costs, or other quantities

name: weight constraint
definition: The weights in GARCH(1,1) must sum to unity: g + a + b = 1

name: weighted aggregation
definition: Using Pi as weights to yield a combined value N

name: weighted average
definition: A method for calculating Dn for coupon-bearing bonds from the Dn's of underlying zero-coupon bonds

name: Weighted average effect for the treated
canonical_name: weighted average effect for the treated
definition: A weighted average treatment effect targeted by the Weakly-targeted design for large values of β

name: weighted average imputation
definition: imputing missing values using a weighted average of the outcomes for other units in the same period

name: weighted average of outcomes
definition: A method of combining outcomes from multiple units using weights to estimate population-level effects

name: weighted average of treated units
definition: A technique for aggregating treatment effects across multiple treated units using weights

name: weighted average of untreated units
definition: A procedural step in synthetic control method where control units are combined with specific weights

name: Weighted Averages of Observed Outcomes
definition: A method for estimating potential outcomes by taking weighted averages of observed outcomes for treated or control units

name: weighted averaging
definition: Using non-stochastic weights to average effects, where weights can down-weight less probable paths and exclude impossible ones

name: Weighted Combination
definition: A method to combine multiple performance index functions using weights wi that sum to 1

name: weighted control subsample
definition: Control units weighted to match treated unit characteristics

name: Weighted difference estimator
definition: An estimator using weights w*_j and v*_j to compute differences in outcomes across units

name: weighted estimation
definition: Estimation method using weighted combinations of periodograms with weights hk

name: weighted ℓ1-penalty
definition: Generalization of ℓ1-penalty with data-adaptive weights

name: weighted link
definition: A connection between two nodes i and j that describes the strength of correlation between their observations

name: weighted nearest neighbour classifiers
definition: A classification method that uses weighted distances to nearest neighbors for prediction

name: weighted outcome combination
definition: Technique of combining outcomes using weights (w*_j and v*_j) to construct treatment effect estimates

name: Weighted outcome comparison
definition: Computing treatment effect as the difference between weighted treated and control outcomes

name: weighted outcome difference
definition: The quantity Σ w*j Yjt - Σ v*j Yjt-τt representing the estimated treatment effect

name: weighted sum
definition: Linear combination of inputs and coefficients

name: weighted sum decomposition
definition: Decomposition of outcome differences into weighted components across units j

name: weighted sum estimator
definition: A technique using weights w* and v* to combine multiple variables or observations

name: Weighted sum of outcomes
definition: Linear combination of weighted random variables ∑ w*j Yjt used in causal inference estimation

name: Weighted sum of random variables
definition: Linear combination of random variables Y_jt with weights w*_j and v*_j

name: Weight estimation
definition: The process of estimating ideal weights (W[i]_v, W[i]_J) in neural networks

name: weighting
definition: A matching approach using weights to balance groups

name: weighting function
definition: A function w over a hypothesis class H defined as w(h) = 1/2^|h| derived from a prefix-free description language.

name: weighting matrix
definition: Matrix used in estimation to weight observations or equations

name: weighting scheme
definition: Assignment of weights to draws based on the ratio of target to proposal density

name: weight matrix
definition: A matrix W that represents the strength of connections between inputs and outputs in a neural network layer

name: weight normalization
definition: Constraints that Σ wj = 1 and Σ vj = 1, normalizing the weights to sum to one

name: weight optimization
definition: The process of optimizing the weights of a neural network model

name: weight renormalization
definition: Renormalizing weights within each leaf and within treatment and control groups to improve efficiency

name: weight rounding
definition: Rounding treated and control weights to the nearest 2-digits to mitigate numerical errors

name: weight selection
definition: The procedure for choosing weights γB_i according to equation (8.19)

name: weight selector
definition: Optimization procedure in equation (6) that selects weights w and v subject to constraints including m ≤ ||v||_0 ≤ m̄

name: Weight Similarity
definition: A criterion for comparing weight vectors based on which units obtain positive weights

name: weights sum to one constraint
definition: The restriction that coefficients in the synthetic control estimator sum to one

name: weight sum constraint
definition: Constraint that w2 + ... + wJ+1 = 1, requiring the sum of all weights to equal one

name: Weights v*_j
definition: Alternative weights applied to outcomes Y_jt

name: Weight swapping
definition: A procedure for exchanging synthetic treated and synthetic control weights when possible without changing objective values

name: Weights w*_j
definition: Optimal weights applied to outcomes Y_jt

name: Weight Trimming
definition: A procedure to reduce extreme weights in weighting estimators

name: weight variability
definition: Property describing how much weights vary; regression weights are less variable than likelihood ratio weights

name: weight vector v
definition: Vector v = (v1, ..., vJ) chosen by experimenter such that sum of vj equals 1

name: weight vector W
definition: A vector in multidimensional space used in optimization problems like SVM

name: welfare analysis
definition: Analysis of economic welfare and policy impacts

name: well-approximability
definition: The assumption that the nuisance parameter can be well-approximated by a particular model class

name: wild bootstrap
definition: A residual bootstrap method that draws X'_i β̂ + ê_i with probability 0.5, and X'_i β̂ - ê_i otherwise, preserving the relationship between residual variances and X_i while imposing mean-independence of residuals and regressors

name: Wild bootstrap inference
definition: A bootstrap method for inference with heteroskedasticity

name: within-leaf treatment effect estimation
definition: estimation of treatment effect τ within leaves of a tree

name: within-leaf variance
definition: The variance computed within each leaf of the tree, denoted as S²_Str(ℓ)

name: with probability 1-o(1)
definition: Probabilistic assumption that an event holds with probability approaching 1 as sample size grows

name: word distribution
definition: The probability distribution of words associated with a topic

name: word embedding
definition: A vector representation of words that captures semantic meaning

name: word embedding methods
definition: Methods that attempt to capture latent semantic structure in language

name: word representation
definition: Representing text at the word level, which requires representing a very large number of classes

name: Word representations via Gaussian embedding
definition: A technique for representing words using Gaussian embeddings

name: Worst case analysis
definition: Analysis of algorithm performance under the most unfavorable conditions

name: worst-case rates
definition: Convergence rates dNT and dNT,∞ of the technical treatment reduced form

name: worst-case risk analysis
definition: Analysis approach focusing on worst-case scenarios rather than confidence intervals

name: wtreat_g
definition: A weight function indexed by treatment group g, dependent on W

name: Xit(α)
definition: Defined as α′(di0(Xit) − di(Xit)), a linear combination of differences in d functions

name: Ŷit
definition: Predicted or estimated outcome variable

name: Yit j
definition: Defined as (li0(Xit) − li(Xit))j, the j-th component of differences in l functions

name: Yi(w)
definition: The outcome corresponding to a level of the treatment w for unit or individual i

name: z*
definition: Critical value from the standard normal distribution used in confidence interval construction

name: Zero mean condition
definition: The assumption that the score function has zero mean at the true parameter value

name: zero natural direct effect assumption
definition: Assumption that ζi(t) = 0 for all t = 0,1 and i, meaning all causal effect operates through the mediator

name: Zero Population Proportion Problem
definition: The difficulty that when the mediator is continuous, the population proportion with Mi(1) = Mi(0) can be essentially zero

name: Z-Estimation
definition: A method to estimate an unknown target parameter θ0 given access to independent replicates of a random data vector satisfying moment conditions

name: Z-estimator
definition: An estimator based on a set of moments, used in the context of the Dynamic DML algorithm

name: Zhang and Zhang (2014) approach
definition: Method for conducting inference on high-dimensional parameters

name: α-regular
definition: Regularity condition for causal forest with α ≤ 0.2

name: α-regular causal tree
definition: A causal tree grown by recursive partitioning where each split leaves at least a fraction α of available training examples on each side, the leaf contains at least k observations from each treatment group, and specific constraints on observation counts are satisfied

name: α-regular tree
definition: A tree with regularity parameter α ≤ 0.2, as defined in Definition 3

name: α-regular tree predictor
definition: A tree predictor grown by recursive partitioning where each split leaves at least a fraction α of available training examples on each side, with trees fully grown to depth k with between k and 2^k-1 observations in terminal nodes

name: β
definition: A parameter that affects the performance of Weakly-targeted and Unit-level designs

name: β0
definition: intercept parameter in linear regression, estimated as Y_n - β1*X_n

name: ∥β0∥ ≤ Cβ
definition: A formal constraint defining that the norm of β0 is bounded by a constant Cβ

name: β (beta parameter)
definition: A parameter β > 0 that reflects the trade-off between fitting treated units to predictors X and fitting control units to match treated units

name: β̂DL
definition: An estimator whose asymptotic distribution is characterized

name: β̂L
definition: Estimated parameter vector from a linear or specific estimation method

name: β-mixing
definition: A mixing condition where coefficients are bounded, used to characterize dependence structure in time series

name: β-mixing coefficient
definition: A measure of weak dependence defined as γX(q) = sup_{m≤M} γ((X1,...,Xm-1,Xm),(Xm+q,Xm+q+1,...))

name: βnev_g,t,δ
definition: A parameter vector indexed by group g, time t, and δ

name: γ-function
definition: A function used in the analysis with various cases considered in corollaries

name: γi(Xit)
definition: Defined as ψi(Xit)ξi(Xit), the product of the differences (di0(Xit) - di(Xit))(li0(Xit) - li(Xit))

name: γ(X)
definition: The outer product ψ(X)ψ(X)′, defined as γ(X) = ψ(X)ψ(X)′

name: γ(Xit)
definition: A function applied to the data Xit, whose norm is bounded in expectation

name: γ(Xmz)
definition: A function applied to data elements Xmz, used in the definitions of M1 and M2

name: δ
definition: Deviation or error vector in the analysis

name: εN = o(1)
definition: The weakest possible rate requirement imposed by Assumption 3.2

name: ϵN-solution
definition: An approximate solution where the estimator θ̃₀ satisfies the inequality condition with tolerance ϵN = o(δN N^(-1/2))

name: ε-overlap
definition: A condition ensuring sufficient overlap in the support of distributions, referenced as equation (6)

name: ζBNT
definition: A convergence rate parameter for bias component

name: ζ E NT,∞
definition: A bound parameter referenced in Lemma 5.2, representing a mathematical quantity in the analysis

name: ζ P NT,∞
definition: A bound parameter appearing in the inequality, representing another mathematical quantity

name: ζVNT
definition: A convergence rate parameter for variance component

name: η
definition: A parameter appearing in the optimization formula

name: θ̌0
definition: An estimator formulation that provides links to classical econometric literature and debiased lasso literature

name: θbal_es
definition: A balanced event-study-type estimand that reports coefficients only for event periods without compositional changes

name: θbal_es(e, e′)
definition: Balanced event study parameter comparing exposure lengths e and e′

name: θc(t̃)
definition: Cohort parameter for specific time period t̃

name: θcumu_c(t̃)
definition: Cumulative treatment effect measure where weights sum to t̃ - 1 rather than one

name: θes
definition: An event-study-type estimand parameter

name: θes(e)
definition: Average effect of participating in treatment e time periods after adoption across all groups observed to have participated for exactly e time periods

name: θO,bal_es(e')
definition: A local single summary parameter representing the average effect of participating in treatment over the first e' periods of exposure

name: θO_c
definition: Average treatment effect aggregated across all time periods, calculated as the mean of θc(t) across all time periods

name: θO_es
definition: Average treatment effect aggregated across all event times, calculated as the mean of θes(e) across all event periods

name: θO_sel
definition: Overall selection-weighted parameter

name: θOsel
definition: A general-purpose summary parameter that computes average effect for each group and then averages across groups, weighted by probability of group membership

name: θO_W
definition: Overall weighted parameter aggregating across all treatment timings and periods

name: θOW
definition: A treatment effect parameter that systematically puts more weight on groups participating in treatment for longer

name: Θps
definition: The parameter space of πg

name: θsel(g̃)
definition: Selection parameter for specific treatment timing g̃

name: κ2(Q,T,c̄)
definition: A conditioning measure or eigenvalue-related quantity used in high-dimensional inference for dynamic panels

name: κNT
definition: √(log³(d² log(NT)) log NT / NT), a convergence rate parameter

name: λ (lambda)
definition: A single parameter that controls the Poisson distribution; represents the intensity or average rate of events

name: µ0
definition: Function that maps the support of (Z, X) to R, representing the structural relationship for outcome Y

name: ν-incremental
definition: Property of predictors where the Hájek projection preserves at least some of the variation of the original predictor

name: ν-incrementality
definition: A weaker form of the variance ratio condition used as an alternative to classical Hájek projection theory for analyzing asymptotic normality

name: ν(s)-incremental
definition: A property of estimator T characterized by rate ν(s) = ε Cf,d log(s)^d

name: ν(s)-incremental predictor
definition: A predictor T is ν(s)-incremental at x if the ratio of variance of its Hájek projection to the variance of T is at least ν(s)

name: ξ
definition: A parameter that affects the performance of Weakly-targeted and Unit-level designs

name: ξi(Xit)
definition: Defined as li0(Xit) - li(Xit), representing the difference between two functions li0 and li

name: ρ
definition: A parameter that is incrementally increased in the interior point method

name: ρj
definition: A parameter representing the maximum absolute deviation from 1, used in bounding analysis

name: σ−1
definition: An inverse variance or scaling parameter with bound ∥σ−1∥= OPN (1)

name: Σ−1/2
definition: Matrix square root inverse, a transformation applied to coefficient estimates

name: σ̂²,mean
definition: Mean variance estimator computed as the average of squared deviations across sample splits

name: σ2-sub-Gaussian random variable
definition: A centered random variable with sub-Gaussian property characterized by parameter σ

name: τ_t^T
definition: A treatment effect parameter being estimated

name: τ(x)
definition: Estimated treatment effect as a function of covariates x

name: τ(x) function
definition: The true underlying function being estimated

name: φ-function
definition: The centered version of γ(X), defined as φ(X) := γ(X) - E[γ(X)] = ψ(X)ψ(X)′ - E[ψ(X)ψ(X)′]

name: φi(Xit)
definition: Defined as γi(Xit) - E[γi(Xit)], the centered version of γi(Xit)

name: φ(X)
definition: Centered random variable defined as γ(X) - Eγ(X), where E denotes expectation

name: φ(Xmz)
definition: A function applied to data elements Xmz, related to γ through equation (F.17)

name: ψh(Wi; θ0, η0)
definition: A function parameterized by θ0 and η0, evaluated at Wi, with subscript h indicating a specific component

name: ψi(Xit)
definition: Defined as (di0(Xit) - di(Xit)), representing the difference between two functions di0 and di

name: ψ(Wi; θ0, η0)
definition: A function of observations Wi with parameters θ0 and η0, with normalized sum having bound ∥N −1/2 PN i=1 ψ(Wi; θ0, η0)∥= OPN (1)

name: ψ(W, θ0, η)
definition: A function defined as µ(X)m(W, θ0, h(Z)) for η = (µ, h)

name: ψ∅(x)
definition: The baseline or intercept term in the log-linear expansion, equal to log p00

name: Ω
definition: A set used in topological analysis, with a closure and complement
